Let the pre-10.12 system clang compile runtime/cgo when a cgo program is built
ON the 10.9 box. Apple's system clang there is clang 6.0 (2014); its
-Wunknown-pragmas warns on the newer diagnostic groups runtime/cgo suppresses
(-Wpragmas, -Watomic-alignment), and runtime/cgo forces -Werror -> a fatal
compile error. Append -Wno-unknown-pragmas last so it wins over the -Werror
earlier on the line. Diagnostic-only, no codegen impact; runtime/cgo is the only
non-test stdlib package that sets -Werror. Harmless with a modern host clang, so
this ships in the cross toolchain too (the std cgo source is compiled on-box on
first use). Provenance: adapted from the predecessor packaging's Makefile
SUBST_CLASSES cgoclang.

--- src/runtime/cgo/cgo.go.orig
+++ src/runtime/cgo/cgo.go
@@ -26,7 +26,7 @@
 // proper support functions. See issues #52919, #54313, #58385.
 // Use -Wdeclaration-after-statement because some CI builds use it.
-#cgo CFLAGS: -Wall -Werror -fno-stack-protector -Wdeclaration-after-statement
+#cgo CFLAGS: -Wall -Werror -fno-stack-protector -Wdeclaration-after-statement -Wno-unknown-pragmas

 #cgo solaris CPPFLAGS: -D_POSIX_PTHREAD_SEMANTICS
